92. Felix Pratensis] An Augus- tinian friar, who being at Rome in 1515 obtained permission from Leo x to make a new translation of the Bible into Latin. The first specimen of this, the Psalter, was printed at Venice, D. Bomberg, 5 Sept. 1515, and con- tains a papal privilege dated 10 Oct. 1515. He also edited for Bomberg a Biblia Rabbinica, 27 Nov. 1518, which has a preface by him to Leo dated 1517.
